radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases are clear. No focal consolidation, nodule, or pleural effusion. Homogenous enhancement of the liver parenchyma without focal lesion. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Hepatic veins and portal venous system are grossly patent. Gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are within normal limits. Symmetric enhancement and excretion of the kidneys without focal lesion or hydronephrosis. Abdominal aorta and its branch vessels are grossly patent and non-aneurysmal. No pathologically enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes. No free fluid or free air. In the right lower quadrant, there is a 12-mm blind-ending, fluid-filled tubular structure with adjacent fat stranding, findings concerning for acute appendicitis. The remainder of the stomach and small bowel are normal in caliber and configuration without evidence of obstruction. The rectum and colon are normal in caliber and configuration without evidence of obstruction. The prostate, seminal vesicles, and bladder are normal. There is a small amount of pelvic free fluid. No pathologically enlarged pelvic or inguinal lymph nodes are identified. No bone destructive lesion or fracture is identified.
